I'll get you another one.

78
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:04,770
Dr. Land?

79
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,820
We're all next door.

80
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:15,360
Yes? What?

81
00:09:15,450 --> 00:09:17,160
Steiner is here.

82
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,990
Get right to it.

83
00:09:22,950 --> 00:09:25,710
Good afternoon, Steiner.

84
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,540
Good afternoon, Doctor.

85
00:09:27,580 --> 00:09:30,550
How was your trip
to New York?

86
00:09:30,590 --> 00:09:32,300
Quite uneventful.

87
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:34,800
The heat was terrible.
God-awful.

88
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:37,260
Not much better here.
Humid.

89
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:40,470
So much
for the weather report.

90
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:43,520
I'm not the only one
who just arrived.

91
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,100
How about your trip
to Berlin, Stick?

92
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,980
It went pretty much
as you figured.

93
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:51,530
Now that, uh,
he's the big star,

94
00:09:51,610 --> 00:09:54,110
I couldn't
reason with him.

95
