The merger
of S & S Records

106
00:10:18,340 --> 00:10:19,930
with Globe
has been completed,

107
00:10:20,010 --> 00:10:21,560
and construction has started

108
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,640
on the new record
pressing plant

109
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:25,060
in Buenos Aires.

110
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,480
But more important
and more immediate

111
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:30,560
is the oncoming
championship fight in Macau.

112
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:33,070
I know we're getting
worldwide press.

113
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:35,990
Steiner:
That and plenty more.

114
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:38,030
All the posters
have been approved

115
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:40,070
and the ad campaign.

116
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,410
The best one
we've ever had.

117
00:10:42,490 --> 00:10:44,950
Looks good.
Looks great.

118
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,040
Besides the gate
and our TV rights,

119
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:51,040
it's generating the kind
of international betting

120
00:10:51,130 --> 00:10:52,670
we'd hoped for.

121
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:55,510
We ought to turn over
about $30 million.

122
00:10:55,590 --> 00:10:58,430
That was the computer's
readout as of today.

123
00:10:58,510 --> 00:11:01,300
Yes, well, the fight
is only 3 weeks off.

124
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:03,060
I assume
your training

125
00:11:03,140 --> 00:11:05,770
is going well, Carl.
You look fit.

126
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:07,730
I'll be ready.

127
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:09,940
We've got a little
problem in Detroit,

128
00:11:10,020 --> 00:11:12,690
a couple of reluctant
ball players.

129
00:11:12,770 --> 00:11:16,440
Hakim, think you can fly
to Detroit and handle that

130
00:11:16,530 --> 00:11:19,030
and be back in time
for the fight?

131
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:21,030
Figure. It's done, man.

132
00:11:21,110 --> 00:11:22,530
Also, I'm afraid

133
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:24,790
we're going to have to do
something about Billy Lo.

134
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:25,990
I was wondering

135
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,080
about that.

136
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:29,080
I was going to ask
how that was going.

137
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,000
Well, he refuses to sign
our management contract,

138
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,750
but that's not
what bothers me now.

139
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:34,540
He's starting
to shoot off his mouth.

140
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,050
He's holding out.

141
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:38,420
Dr. Land:
We've given him so many chances--

142
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:40,430
an amazing amount
of resistance.

143
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:42,590
And then there's
that girlfriend:

144
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:43,850
Ann Morris.

145
00:11:43,890 --> 00:11:45,850
I went to talk
to her today.

146
00:11:45,930 --> 00:11:47,520
Her last album
was on the charts

147
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,850
and is doing great

148
00:11:48,930 --> 00:11:50,190
in Australia
and France.

149
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:51,850
She says she wants
to talk to Billy

150
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:54,190
about her contract
before she signs.

151
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:57,780
Doctor, I think we ought
to squeeze a little.

152
00:11:59,490 --> 00:12:01,070
Dr. Land:
Yeah, let's just

153
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,860
squeeze a little,

154
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:05,200
wouldn't you say?

155
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,830
Billy?

156
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:08,450
Yeah.

157
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:10,040
I had another visit today

158
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,080
from one
of those syndicate men.

159
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:13,540
Did he threaten you?

160
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:15,040
Well, not exactly.

161
00:12:15,130 --> 00:12:17,420
I mean,
not in so many words,

162
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:20,050
but I knew
I was being threatened.

163
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:23,090
Billy, do you think
it's worth holding out?

164
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:24,590
I mean, I've heard

165
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:27,390
some pretty ugly things
about those guys,

166
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,640
ugly stories.

167
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:53,540
If we're stopped,
don't do anything

168
00:12:53,580 --> 00:12:55,210
that will give them

169
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:57,170
an excuse
to hurt you.

170
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,060
Ann, I love you,

171
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:11,060
and I don't
want you hurt.

172
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:12,770
Trust me
to handle this.

173
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:19,110
Billy:
I would like Miss Morris to leave.

174
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:21,610
I'm afraid we can't
do that, Billy.

175
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:23,240
We're all
in this together.

176
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,780
Now, would you mind

177
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:26,570
stepping out
of the car?

178
00:13:26,620 --> 00:13:28,580
No matter what happens,

179
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:30,950
don't get out of the car.

180
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,040
You've got until

181
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,800
tomorrow morning
to call us.

182
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,250
It's the last time

183
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,920
we're going to ask,
Billy.

184
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:44,510
Billy!

185
00:13:56,730 --> 00:13:57,480
No!

186
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:16,790
Billy.

187
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,220
Hyah!

188
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:34,680
Please stop it!

189
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:45,240
Please don't!

190
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,320
Billy.

191
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,040
Billy!

192
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:07,760
He hasn't
got too much time.

193
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,220
You tell him that.

194
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,220
We want
to hear from him

195
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:12,640
in the morning.

196
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:38,540
Billy, I've always
been straight with you.

197
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:40,750
You don't have
too many choices.

198
00:15:40,830 --> 00:15:43,340
You and Ann
are nothing to them.

199
00:15:43,420 --> 00:15:44,920
You're just
another piece of property,

200
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,510
just one
of a couple of thousand

201
00:15:47,590 --> 00:15:50,590
of public personalities
that they own all of

202
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:53,010
or a piece of.

203
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:56,390
It seems like
a good thing at the moment.

204
00:15:56,430 --> 00:15:58,770
They take care
of everything--

205
00:15:58,810 --> 00:16:00,060
your booking,

206
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:01,600
your salary, your taxes.

207
00:16:01,650 --> 00:16:03,520
If you need 5, 000
in your pocket,

208
00:16:03,610 --> 00:16:05,360
you've got it.

209
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,530
It's later

210
00:16:06,610 --> 00:16:08,280
that you start to realize

211
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,950
what it's costing you.

212
00:16:10,150 --> 00:16:13,120
I don't have to remind you
about Charlie Wang.

213
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,530
We know the pressure
they put on him,

214
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:18,200
and we know they
called him in for a "talk."

215
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:20,540
Hyah!

216
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:22,040
The next day,

217
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,960
he was fished
out of the harbor.

218
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:28,380
But going along with them
isn't much better.

219
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,130
You've come up
fast, Billy.

220
00:17:07,170 --> 00:17:10,340
The pictures are grossing big
all over the world.

221
00:17:10,420 --> 00:17:13,510
You're an international
celebrity,

222
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:15,840
and they smell
that money.

223
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:17,510
Thank you.

224
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,510
You can sign
with them

225
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:22,020
and live very well,
or you can defy them

226
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,690
and go
to the police,

227
00:17:23,770 --> 00:17:26,020
which means you
won't live so well,

228
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,190
if at all.

229
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:30,440
Is it your advice
to let them own us?

230
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:33,030
No. I just

231
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:36,530
don't want to write
an obituary on you.

232
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,620
I like you too much,

233
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:40,120
which is my cue

234
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,870
to get my ass
down to the bureau.

235
00:17:41,950 --> 00:17:43,580
I've got
a midnight deadline

236
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:45,040
for the States.

237
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:48,840
I can't allow it.

238
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:51,960
It is better to die
a broken piece of jade

239
00:17:52,050 --> 00:17:54,550
than to live a life of clay.

240
00:17:54,630 --> 00:17:57,340
Quit. You've got
enough money.

241
00:17:57,430 --> 00:17:59,350
Tell them to go to hell.

242
00:17:59,430 --> 00:18:01,390
Ann:
I can leave this all behind.

243
00:18:01,470 --> 00:18:02,810
I don't
need this

244
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:04,350
if you
don't need it.

245
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:12,530
There has
to be another answer.

246
00:18:12,570 --> 00:18:14,490
I've got to find one.

247
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:26,870
Ann:
The Chinese opera is in town.

248
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,250
Maybe see your uncle.

249
00:18:28,290 --> 00:18:30,250
Yeah, he just got back.

250
00:18:30,290 --> 00:18:32,420
I'll go to the theater tomorrow.
Good idea.

251
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,970
All three of them
are leaving the restaurant.

252
00:18:35,050 --> 00:18:36,510
What should we do?

253
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:38,010
Dr. Land:
Don't lose them.

254
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:47,310
Steiner:
Alegandre, from now on,

255
00:18:47,390 --> 00:18:48,730
I want you to coordinate

256
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:50,900
all your efforts with
the ad agency in New York.

257
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:53,780
And by the way, what are
the odds where you are now?

258
00:18:53,820 --> 00:18:55,780
Well, then keep
the publicity going

259
00:18:55,860 --> 00:18:57,450
about Carl's rumored
sprained ligament.

260
00:18:57,530 --> 00:18:58,860
Don't give the impression

261
00:18:58,950 --> 00:19:00,820
that the fight's
going to be canceled,

262
00:19:00,910 --> 00:19:02,200
just that he's in pain

263
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:03,790
and might be
at a disadvantage.

264
00:19:03,870 --> 00:19:05,000
You got that?

265
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,870
Ciao.

266
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:10,380
The odds are a little
too heavy on Carl,

267
00:19:10,460 --> 00:19:12,340
especially in London.

268
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:15,840
Yes, a good idea
to even that up a bit.

269
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,720
Oh, by the way,

270
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,470
what about Billy Lo?

271
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:22,890
He was told to
call earlier today.

272
00:19:22,970 --> 00:19:24,810
He has
the number to call.

273
00:19:24,850 --> 00:19:27,140
Oh, do we know where
he is at this moment?

274
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:29,640
Well, we always know
where he is.

275
00:19:29,730 --> 00:19:32,610
Well, then
a final warning,

276
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:33,730
Ok, Carl?

277
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:38,280
Yes, Pasqual.
You go with him.

278
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:39,650
[ Chuckling ]

279
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:43,030
Pasqual
loves to fight, yes.

280
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:45,040
Ha ha.

281
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:25,450
Let me use your brush.
Thanks.

282
00:20:27,870 --> 00:20:29,450
Man:
Billy, good to see you.

283
00:20:29,540 --> 00:20:31,460
Billy:
Hi, John. I'm glad you're back.

284
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:33,130
Your uncle
is in his room.

285
00:20:42,050 --> 00:20:44,340
Billy. Come in, Billy.

286
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:46,390
Come in. Hey. Hey!

287
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:47,760
You go ahead.

288
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:50,810
It's good to see you, boy.
Sit down. Sit down.

289
00:20:50,890 --> 00:20:53,060
[ Clears Throat ]

290
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,360
We do not see you much

291
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,610
since you got to be
a big man.

292
00:20:57,690 --> 00:20:59,110
Oh, yes, I know.

293
00:20:59,190 --> 00:21:01,650
I've been running
for months.

294
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:03,570
Yeah, very busy, huh?

295
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,580
I heard that the syndicate
is after you.

296
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:09,790
You must be a big man.

297
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:11,410
How did you
know that?

298
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:14,370
It's
a small business.

299
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:15,880
I can't join them,

300
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,750
and I can't
be forced to join.

301
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,920
You have just
described a problem

302
00:21:20,010 --> 00:21:21,420
as old as man.

303
00:21:21,510 --> 00:21:22,880
You're not unique.

304
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:25,430
There is a solution

305
00:21:25,510 --> 00:21:28,930
I do not think
you've considered.

306
00:21:29,010 --> 00:21:31,430
When you get to the top,

307
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:34,440
you understand
how far it is to fall,

308
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:37,940
but if you think
very little of yourself,

309
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:39,940
then you can be pushed off

310
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:41,570
and fall very easily.

311
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:46,450
What is your opinion
of yourself?.

312
00:21:46,490 --> 00:21:49,660
I believe I deserve
to be where I am.

313
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:51,870
I've worked
hard for it.

314
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:53,410
Then don't let them push.

315
00:21:53,460 --> 00:21:55,580
They will never
let you rest.

316
00:21:55,620 --> 00:21:56,960
You push.

317
00:21:57,040 --> 00:22:00,000
You mean kill?

318
00:22:01,670 --> 00:22:03,920
Integrity can be
an expensive thing.

319
00:22:03,970 --> 00:22:06,470
What is the price
of your integrity?

320
00:22:06,510 --> 00:22:08,510
What are you
willing to pay?

321
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:11,010
There is another
person as well,

322
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,020
a girl.

323
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,100
If I fight,
she may be hurt.

324
00:22:14,180 --> 00:22:15,480
Send her away.

325
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,650
Do you need help?

326
00:22:17,730 --> 00:22:20,480
I know some men
who can help you.

327
00:22:20,570 --> 00:22:22,070
No.

328
00:22:22,190 --> 00:22:24,440
You're not allowed
back here.

329
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:26,530
Get out! Get out!

330
00:22:26,610 --> 00:22:30,160
[ Woman Screams ]

331
00:23:16,870 --> 00:23:19,330
Another message, Billy.

332
00:23:23,250 --> 00:23:25,510
The Chinese syndicate
wants to make sure

333
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:27,260
they're riding
with a winner,

334
00:23:27,340 --> 00:23:29,800
so they're willing to
buy a little insurance.

335
00:23:29,890 --> 00:23:32,640
A million and a half
dollars in cash

336
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:34,890
will be arriving
in Macau

337
00:23:34,970 --> 00:23:36,850
just before the fight.

338
00:23:36,890 --> 00:23:39,060
They're going to drop it

339
00:23:39,140 --> 00:23:41,150
right on your doorstep.

340
00:23:41,230 --> 00:23:43,150
Clean money?

341
00:23:43,230 --> 00:23:44,150
Oh, yeah.

342
00:23:44,230 --> 00:23:46,570
Yeah, very crisp
and very clean.

343
00:23:46,650 --> 00:23:48,740
The cash started out
in Nassau.

344
00:23:48,820 --> 00:23:50,950
It's going through
Tommy's bank in Mexico City

345
00:23:51,030 --> 00:23:52,200
right now.

346
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:54,790
We're watching
its progress.

347
00:23:54,870 --> 00:23:56,450
Fine. Fine.

348
00:23:56,540 --> 00:23:57,790
Oh, Carl.

349
00:23:57,870 --> 00:23:59,250
Yes, sir.

350
00:23:59,290 --> 00:24:00,620
What about Billy Lo?

351
00:24:00,710 --> 00:24:02,000
What's happened
there?

352
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:03,880
Nothing. Not a word.

353
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:06,210
He's not going to call.

354
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:09,050
Rebellion is contagious,
Doctor.

355
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:11,340
Let's close the book.

356
00:24:11,430 --> 00:24:13,100
[ Chuckles Softly ]

357
00:24:13,180 --> 00:24:16,220
What an
unfortunate waste,

358
00:24:16,310 --> 00:24:20,100
casting aside
his life like that.

359
00:24:20,190 --> 00:24:22,480
What a pity.

360
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:24,230
[ Telephone Rings ]

361
00:24:24,310 --> 00:24:25,480
Hello.

362
00:24:25,570 --> 00:24:26,940
Billy:
Hello, Ann. It's me.

363
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,610
Billy, where have you been?

364
00:24:28,690 --> 00:24:30,740
I've been trying
to reach you all day.

365
00:24:30,820 --> 00:24:32,200
I've been worried
about you.

366
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,320
I've been worried

367
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:34,570
about you, too,
darling.

368
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:35,780
Ann, listen
carefully.

369
00:24:35,870 --> 00:24:36,990
I want you
to meet me

370
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,160
on the 6:00 ferry.

371
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:39,660
You'll find me

372
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:41,000
in the passenger
section.

373
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:42,250
Do you understand?

374
00:24:42,330 --> 00:24:43,920
Ok. Billy,
are you all right?

375
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,840
Yes. To tell
the truth,

376
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,420
I feel
much better now.

377
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:55,320
Billy.

378
00:26:00,370 --> 00:26:02,000
Billy, you've
been hurt.

379
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,750
It doesn't matter.

380
00:26:03,830 --> 00:26:05,580
Ann, I want you

381
00:26:05,670 --> 00:26:08,250
to go back to
the States for a while.

382
00:26:08,340 --> 00:26:09,840
Leave you here?

383
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:12,260
I have to work
this problem out by myself.

384
00:26:12,340 --> 00:26:14,590
It would only
be for a while,

385
00:26:14,670 --> 00:26:16,510
a couple of months.

386
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:18,600
No way, Billy.

387
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:20,470
I can't do that.

388
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:22,180
Look, you can't help me,

389
00:26:22,270 --> 00:26:24,520
but if you stay,
I can hurt you.

390
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,520
Maybe you
should change your name

391
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:28,110
and disappear for a while.

392
00:26:28,190 --> 00:26:30,520
I have only one scene
left in this film.

393
00:26:30,570 --> 00:26:32,610
I'll be dropping
out of sight myself.

394
00:26:35,070 --> 00:26:37,610
Billy, I can't
leave you.

395
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:39,280
What are you
up to?

396
00:26:39,370 --> 00:26:41,200
Not a thing.

397
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:43,200
We have to separate.

398
00:26:47,420 --> 00:26:51,550
Ann, I'd like to live
with you a long time,

399
00:26:51,630 --> 00:26:53,590
you know?

400
00:26:53,630 --> 00:26:55,340
Grow old together.

401
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:58,390
Ann, On Telephone:
It was very strange.

402
00:26:58,470 --> 00:27:00,050
Not like him,
very secretive.

403
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:02,220
It sounds like he's
made a decision to run,

404
00:27:02,310 --> 00:27:03,810
which would be smart.

405
00:27:03,890 --> 00:27:05,560
No, I don't think
he's running at all.

406
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:07,100
I think it's
just the opposite.

407
00:27:07,140 --> 00:27:08,480
There was
a determination

408
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,150
about him, like he
was going to fight.

409
00:27:10,230 --> 00:27:11,610
Jim, I know
he has a call

410
00:27:11,650 --> 00:27:13,110
at the studio
this afternoon.

411
00:27:13,150 --> 00:27:14,610
Would you mind
meeting me there?

412
00:27:14,650 --> 00:27:16,030
I'm really worried
about him.

413
00:27:16,110 --> 00:27:17,900
Of course.
I'll be right over.

414
00:27:17,950 --> 00:27:18,910
Stage 4.

415
00:27:18,950 --> 00:27:20,320
Yeah. I got you.

416
00:27:20,410 --> 00:27:21,740
David.

417
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,950
Yeah.

418
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,580
Keep it
together.

419
00:27:27,410 --> 00:27:28,540
Man: Cut.

420
00:27:28,620 --> 00:27:29,960
Print it.

421
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:33,130
Ok, turn around,
guys.

422
00:27:33,210 --> 00:27:34,880
Let's set up
for Billy's run.

423
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,630
Second Man:
Ok, move it along.

424
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:38,340
Get ready
for the reverse angle.

425
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:39,590
Let's go, fellas.

426
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:45,140
Gentlemen,
these are blanks.

427
00:27:45,180 --> 00:27:47,060
Only aim upward.

428
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:49,560
There's a wad of paper
that comes out

429
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:51,560
and can injure someone.

430
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:07,080
[ Knock On Door ]

431
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:09,410
We're ready for you,
Billy.

432
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:10,460
Ok.

433
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:22,640
Director:
Now, I want you

434
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:25,350
to come running out
of the building like hell.

435
00:28:25,430 --> 00:28:27,470
I'll cue the guns
on your leap,

436
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:29,230
and you do the fall, ok?

437
00:28:29,310 --> 00:28:31,190
Ok, let's
walk through it once.

438
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:37,110
Ann:
Billy, over here.

439
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:40,610
What are you doing here?

440
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:42,280
Take her
to the airport, Jim.

441
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:45,120
Billy, something
isn't reading right.

442
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,830
Do you need help?

443
00:28:46,910 --> 00:28:48,870
I'm going
to break it wide open.

444
00:28:48,950 --> 00:28:50,540
The police
have got to get into it.

445
00:28:50,620 --> 00:28:52,920
And when it explodes,
I don't want Ann here.

446
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,840
Get her on a plane.

447
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:57,590
Billy--

448
00:28:57,670 --> 00:28:59,050
Please, Jim.

449
00:29:01,550 --> 00:29:02,840
Here we go.

450
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,140
Man:
Everybody settle down. Ready.

451
00:29:04,140 --> 00:29:05,970
Man:
Everybody settle down. Ready.

452
00:29:08,770 --> 00:29:10,560
Director:
Ok, ready to roll.

453
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:13,060
Ok. This is a take.

454
00:29:13,150 --> 00:29:14,900
Quiet, please.

455
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:21,700
Ok, roll sound.

456
00:29:21,780 --> 00:29:23,570
[ Men Speaking Chinese ]

457
00:29:26,740 --> 00:29:27,830
Action!

458
00:29:32,410 --> 00:29:34,040
[ Yelling ]

459
00:29:44,430 --> 00:29:50,680
Waah...

460
00:29:50,770 --> 00:29:53,310
[ Gunshot ]

461
00:29:53,390 --> 00:29:56,610
Director:
Hey, Billy, what's the matter?

462
00:29:56,690 --> 00:29:58,940
Hey, what's happening here?

463
00:29:59,020 --> 00:30:00,320
What happened?

464
00:30:03,490 --> 00:30:04,950
What's wrong?

465
00:30:04,990 --> 00:30:06,570
My, God! He's hurt.

466
00:30:06,660 --> 00:30:08,740
[ Ann Screaming ]

467
00:30:08,780 --> 00:30:10,790
Somebody call a doctor!

468
00:30:10,870 --> 00:30:12,580
Don't just stand there!

469
00:30:12,660 --> 00:30:15,620
[ Siren ]

470
00:30:19,340 --> 00:30:20,630
The bullet fragmented

471
00:30:20,710 --> 00:30:22,510
as it passed through
at an upward angle,

472
00:30:22,590 --> 00:30:23,920
literally smashing

473
00:30:23,970 --> 00:30:26,340
the bone structure
of the face.

474
00:30:26,430 --> 00:30:27,840
What are his chances

475
00:30:27,930 --> 00:30:30,430
of having
a normal appearance?

476
00:30:30,510 --> 00:30:31,640
There'll be

477
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:33,600
extensive
structural changes,

478
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,600
a great deal
of scar tissue.

479
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:37,940
He'll be permanently
altered, of course,

480
00:30:38,020 --> 00:30:40,150
but presentable,
in any case.

481
00:30:40,230 --> 00:30:41,150
Hmm.

482
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:43,990
Thank you, Doctor.

483
00:30:58,170 --> 00:30:59,790
Jim:
Hey, Billy,

484
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,550
are you awake?

485
00:31:01,630 --> 00:31:02,840
Yes.

486
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:05,630
I've been talking
with your surgeon.

487
00:31:05,670 --> 00:31:08,300
The surgery
will be tomorrow.

488
00:31:08,340 --> 00:31:10,640
This is
a very private hospital.

489
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,310
No one will know.

490
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,350
Billy:
Good.

491
00:31:13,430 --> 00:31:14,520
Then you still want

492
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,390
to go through
with this?

493
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:17,810
Yes.

494
00:31:17,850 --> 00:31:20,310
The only reason I've
considered this,

495
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:22,820
Mr. Lo, is
the simple argument:

496
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:24,690
Should you walk
upon the street,

497
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:26,320
undoubtedly
there will be

498
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,990
another attempt
upon your life.

499
00:31:28,070 --> 00:31:30,030
Then you agree?

500
00:31:30,070 --> 00:31:32,030
There'll have
to be a complete

501
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:33,450
falsification
of documents,

502
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:34,750
death certificate,

503
00:31:34,830 --> 00:31:35,950
and somebody

504
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,660
will have
to inform the press

505
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:40,170
you've taken a turn
for the worse--

506
00:31:40,210 --> 00:31:42,170
Relapse. Then
there's the question

507
00:31:42,210 --> 00:31:43,840
of a change
of identity.

508
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,420
A new identification

509
00:31:45,510 --> 00:31:47,300
has already
been taken care of.

510
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:50,430
We should tell Ann.

511
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:53,470
No.

512
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:57,100
No one else must know.

513
00:31:57,180 --> 00:32:00,190
If she knows,
she could be in danger.

514
00:32:00,230 --> 00:32:02,610
A public funeral?
Open casket?

515
00:32:02,690 --> 00:32:05,150
After all,
he is a celebrity.

516
00:32:05,230 --> 00:32:07,110
Don't worry, John.

517
00:32:07,190 --> 00:32:09,570
It'll be a very
believable funeral.

518
00:33:31,990 --> 00:33:33,490
[ Clears Throat ]

519
00:33:33,570 --> 00:33:36,200
They have some
interesting people here.

520
00:33:39,660 --> 00:33:41,750
It could be a story.

521
00:33:55,340 --> 00:33:56,760
Miss Morris.

522
00:33:56,850 --> 00:33:58,640
[ Spits ]

523
00:33:58,680 --> 00:33:59,930
Carl:
You're dead.

524
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:01,100
Come on, Ann.

525
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:03,100
Do you hear me?
You're dead.

526
00:34:03,190 --> 00:34:05,100
Cool it.

527
00:34:05,190 --> 00:34:07,360
Excuse us. Thank you.

528
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:09,690
Let us through. Easy.

529
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:13,030
Thank you.

530
00:34:15,030 --> 00:34:16,660
Jim:
No, Ann.

531
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:20,790
For $10, he could
have you killed.

532
00:34:20,870 --> 00:34:23,330
Yes, I understand.
It's cheap.

533
00:34:23,410 --> 00:34:25,120
I'm glad
you understand,

534
00:34:25,210 --> 00:34:27,130
and I'm glad

535
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:29,540
you're pulling
yourself together.

536
00:34:29,630 --> 00:34:31,550
Oh, no. I'm not
going to cry anymore.

537
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:32,840
God knows

538
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:35,630
the police would
like to nail them...

539
00:34:37,390 --> 00:34:39,970
but there's
no way to prove it.

540
00:34:40,060 --> 00:34:43,640
Don't you understand
anything?!

541
00:34:43,730 --> 00:34:46,100
Everybody looked at them,

542
00:34:46,190 --> 00:34:49,480
but not one person
could see anything!

543
00:35:08,670 --> 00:35:09,790
The gentlemen

544
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:11,170
from the
Chinese syndicate

545
00:35:11,250 --> 00:35:13,210
and the cash have
arrived in Macau.

546
00:35:13,260 --> 00:35:15,550
Fine, fine. Now, you
sure it's a good idea,

547
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:17,130
our stopping
in the sanitarium

548
00:35:17,220 --> 00:35:18,590
to see this Morris girl?

549
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,050
She's
a very valuable

550
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:21,390
piece of
merchandise.

551
00:35:21,470 --> 00:35:23,430
And if we can bring
her into the family,

552
00:35:23,470 --> 00:35:24,810
it will show

553
00:35:24,890 --> 00:35:26,390
all the other
would-be rebels

554
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:27,940
how complete
our control is.

555
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:49,710
Woman: You go ahead.
I'll see you later.

556
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:51,710
Hello, Mr. Marshall.

557
00:35:51,790 --> 00:35:53,500
Hello, Doctor. How's Ann?

558
00:35:53,590 --> 00:35:55,590
We're very pleased
with her recovery.

559
00:35:55,630 --> 00:35:57,880
It's been, um...

560
00:35:57,970 --> 00:36:00,090
a long haul.

561
00:36:00,180 --> 00:36:01,300
3 weeks?

562
00:36:01,390 --> 00:36:02,300
Mm-hmm.

563
00:36:02,390 --> 00:36:03,890
For a trauma
severe enough

564
00:36:03,970 --> 00:36:05,600
to bring on
physical paralysis,

565
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:07,600
a 3-week recovery
is extremely good.

566
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:10,100
Oh, well, may
I go down to see her?

567
00:36:10,150 --> 00:36:11,940
Absolutely.
If you hadn't come out,

568
00:36:11,980 --> 00:36:13,610
I would
have called you.

569
00:36:13,650 --> 00:36:15,610
She's ready to see
a familiar face.

570
00:36:15,650 --> 00:36:16,900
You must understand

571
00:36:16,990 --> 00:36:18,610
she's
still depressed.

572
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:29,290
Is it time to go in?

573
00:36:29,370 --> 00:36:30,370
Hi, Annie.

574
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:31,380
Jim.

575
00:36:31,460 --> 00:36:33,290
[ Chuckles Softly ]

576
00:36:33,340 --> 00:36:36,380
Oh, I brought you
a little present.

577
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:37,920
I-It's beautiful.

578
00:36:38,010 --> 00:36:40,130
I hear nothing
but good things about you.

579
00:36:40,180 --> 00:36:41,300
No lies?

580
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:42,300
No lies.

581
00:36:42,340 --> 00:36:44,760
Would
a newspaperman lie?

582
00:36:44,850 --> 00:36:46,890
Now I'm
getting worried.

583
00:36:46,970 --> 00:36:48,560
But, Jim, actually,

584
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:50,390
I'm feeling
a lot better.

585
00:36:50,480 --> 00:36:51,400
Good.

586
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,400
At least

587
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:53,980
I'm able to deal
with people now.

588
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:02,070
You know, maybe you
should get out of here,

589
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:05,580
go back to the States when
you're feeling better, hmm?

590
00:37:05,660 --> 00:37:08,080
I've been thinking
about that, too,

591
00:37:08,160 --> 00:37:10,620
but I
don't want to yet.

592
00:37:13,170 --> 00:37:15,540
Not just yet.

593
00:37:15,630 --> 00:37:17,250
Yes, but more
important than that,

594
00:37:17,340 --> 00:37:18,420
I think we ought

595
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:19,880
to try
to see for ourselves

596
00:37:19,970 --> 00:37:21,340
what's going on
in her head,

597
00:37:21,380 --> 00:37:22,590
what kind
of a threat

598
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:23,840
she could be to us.

599
00:37:23,930 --> 00:37:25,600
I don't want to
leave that to Carl

600
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:26,760
or to anybody else.

601
00:37:26,850 --> 00:37:27,810
We're here.

602
00:37:27,890 --> 00:37:30,100
There.

603
00:37:30,180 --> 00:37:31,980
Steiner:
That's the newspaperman,

604
00:37:32,060 --> 00:37:33,690
Jim Marshall.
You know, I've got

605
00:37:33,730 --> 00:37:35,400
a hunch that
one of these days,

606
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:37,070
we're going
to have to cram

607
00:37:37,150 --> 00:37:38,610
his typewriter
up his ass.

608
00:37:38,690 --> 00:37:39,820
Oh?

609
00:37:44,530 --> 00:37:46,530
It's the blonde.

610
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:05,390
Good afternoon,
Miss Morris.

611
00:38:06,930 --> 00:38:08,390
We haven't
officially met,

612
00:38:08,430 --> 00:38:10,770
but my name is Steiner.
This is Dr. Land.

613
00:38:10,850 --> 00:38:12,520
How do you do,
Miss Morris?

614
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:15,020
We were informed
of your improvement.

615
00:38:15,100 --> 00:38:17,860
Oh, you
are so beautiful.

616
00:38:17,940 --> 00:38:18,900
Beautiful.

617
00:38:18,940 --> 00:38:20,650
What do you want?

618
00:38:20,730 --> 00:38:22,190
We were just passing by.

619
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,150
We wondered if we
could do anything for you.

620
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:26,280
Is there something
you might need?

621
00:38:26,370 --> 00:38:27,740
There's nothing I need, ok?

622
00:38:27,820 --> 00:38:29,910
Your album is doing
very well on the charts.

623
00:38:29,950 --> 00:38:31,660
It's going
to make lots of money.

624
00:38:31,750 --> 00:38:33,160
We know,
Miss Morris,

625
00:38:33,250 --> 00:38:35,000
what has happened--
the terrible strain

626
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,830
that you
have been under.

627
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:38,880
We hope
that possibly

628
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,670
we can
assist somehow.

629
00:38:40,750 --> 00:38:41,670
You know,

630
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:43,670
maybe get your
career moving again.

631
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:44,930
Get out!

632
00:38:45,010 --> 00:38:46,180
There's nothing--

633
00:38:46,260 --> 00:38:47,390
Get out!

634
00:38:47,470 --> 00:38:50,350
It's Dr. Land's intention
to try to help you, Ann.

635
00:38:50,430 --> 00:38:51,600
He could be--

636
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:52,930
You murderers!

637
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:54,980
Get out of here.

638
00:38:55,020 --> 00:38:55,940
Get out!

639
00:38:56,020 --> 00:38:57,350
[ Growls ]

640
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:59,060
Get out of here!

641
00:39:00,980 --> 00:39:03,940
Rude bitch.

642
00:39:03,990 --> 00:39:06,450
Well, one rebel
begets another.

643
00:39:06,490 --> 00:39:08,450
It's the Billy Lo
syndrome.

644
00:39:08,490 --> 00:39:11,450
A virulent disease,

645
00:39:11,490 --> 00:39:14,200
often terminal.

646
00:39:14,290 --> 00:39:16,830
Steiner:
Stick, she seemed to know you.

647
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,830
Your face did
something for her.

648
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,250
Never met her.

649
00:39:20,340 --> 00:39:22,000
We have to go to Macau.

650
00:39:22,090 --> 00:39:24,460
We'll see about her
when we return.

651
00:39:27,180 --> 00:39:29,800
Grr. Bitch!

652
00:39:40,690 --> 00:39:42,980
What are you up to,
Billy?

653
00:39:43,030 --> 00:39:45,990
I'm giving myself
a new face...

654
00:39:46,030 --> 00:39:48,280
before and after.

655
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:50,490
Much better.

656
00:39:50,530 --> 00:39:52,160
I've already
told you, Billy.

657
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:54,490
You're going to have
a normal appearance again.

658
00:39:54,540 --> 00:39:56,120
You'll see.
Wait till tomorrow

659
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:57,830
when those bandages
come off.

660
00:39:57,870 --> 00:39:59,170
P.A.:
Dr. Ferguson,

661
00:39:59,250 --> 00:40:00,710
please report
to the nurses' station.

662
00:40:00,750 --> 00:40:02,500
Well, excuse me.

663
00:40:02,540 --> 00:40:05,630
Dr. Ferguson, please report
to the nurses' station.

664
00:40:05,710 --> 00:40:07,420
The new Billy Lo.

665
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:05,110
Mister,
can I hire you

666
00:41:05,190 --> 00:41:06,780
